{
  "body": "You are designing a whimsical and vibrant layered paper-cut illustration.\n\nCONTENT BRIEF\n- Primary subject: {{subject}}\n- Backdrop or setting: {{setting}}\n- Optional copy: {{copy}}\n\nSTYLE DIRECTION\n- Genre / medium: Digital illustration emulating layered paper-cut artwork\n- Composition: Side-profile or centered subject, with a balanced layout of layered elements; high negative space usage and clean separation between subject and backdrop\n- Lens / camera: Flat perspective with no depth of field; all layers equally sharp\n- Lighting: Diffuse ambient light with soft shadows between paper layers for depth\n- Color palette and grading: Vibrant pastel tones, with warm and cool color contrasts (yellow, orange, pink, blue, purple); high saturation\n- Texture / surface: Smooth paper-like textures, subtle gradients for realism\n- Post-processing: Clean and polished, no grain or noise; precise shadow edges for paper-layer effect\n- Mood: Whimsical, playful, elegant, modern\n- References: Modern paper art styles, vector-based digital illustrations, crisp and colorful design language\n\nDESIGN RULES\n- Aspect: 2:3 portrait (~1024×1536) suitable for posters, editorial covers, or vertical displays\n- Ensure subject is the focal point with surrounding layered elements complementing the design\n- Keep all elements cleanly separated; avoid clutter or overly complex layering\n\nAVOID\n- Harsh or direct lighting\n- Overlapping layers that obscure details\n- Dull or desaturated color schemes\n- Excessive or uneven shadowing\n- Realistic textures that break the paper illusion\n- Gradients or effects that obscure the clean paper-cut style\n\nAdditional constraints: {{extra}}\n\n——————\nSubject: {{subject}}\nSetting: {{setting}}\nCopy: {{copy}}\nExtra notes: {{extra}}",
